title: Number of deaths in Libyan city of Derna could reach 20,000, mayor says
description: The number of deaths in the Libyan city of Derna could range from 18,000 to 20,000 following catastrophic flooding, according to the city's mayor.

title: Earth exceeding 'safe operating space for humanity'
description: Earth is exceeding its "safe operating space for humanity" in six of nine key measurements of its health, and two of the remaining three are heading in the wrong direction, a new study has said.

title: Elon Musk refuses to answer if his 'ignorance and ego' cost Ukrainian lives
description: Billionaire Elon Musk has refused to answer Sky News questions about claims he foiled a Ukrainian attack on Russian warships.

title: El Chapo's wife released after serving less than two years in US prison
description: The wife of Mexican drug kingpin Joaquin "El Chapo" Guzman has been freed from US federal custody after serving less than two years in prison for her involvement in his multibillion-dollar criminal operation.

title: Baltic states ban vehicles with Russian number plates
description: Estonia has joined fellow Baltic states Latvia and Lithuania in banning vehicles with Russian number plates from entering their territory.

title: Sara Sharif's father, stepmother and uncle arrested on suspicion of murder
description: Sara Sharif's father, stepmother and uncle have been arrested on suspicion of murder in connection with the death of the 10-year-old girl.

title: Three adults sought by police over Sara Sharif's death flying back to UK from Pakistan
description: Three adults who British police want to speak to in connection with the death of Sara Sharif are returning to the UK from Pakistan.

title: 1,000 year-old 'alien corpses' displayed in glass cases
description: Two alleged "non-human" alien corpses have been shown to Mexican politicians.

title: Harry and Meghan in high spirits at Invictus Games
description: Cheering and waving from the stands, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex enjoyed a game of wheelchair basketball at the Invictus Games in Germany.

title: Before and after pictures show devastation of Libya floods
description: Satellite images have shown the devastation caused by catastrophic flooding in Libya which has seen neighbourhoods washed away and killed thousands of people.

title: At least 30,000 displaced after Libya floods - with fatalities expected to rise significantly
description: At least 30,000 people have been displaced in the town hardest hit by floods in Libya.

title: British cruise missiles were used in significant Ukrainian attack on Russian submarine
description: Ukraine used British cruise missiles in a significant attack against the headquarters of Russia's Black Sea Fleet in occupied Crimea, Sky News understands.

title: UK 'closely monitoring' spread of fatal cow disease in Europe
description: Authorities in the UK say they are "closely monitoring" the spread of a disease that can be deadly to cattle.

title: North Korea supports Russia's 'sacred fight' against the West, Kim tells Putin
description: Kim Jong Un has pledged his support to Russia in what he has described as the "fight against imperialism".
